---
/**
 * Guided walk — Chapter 1 of 5: "Who is actually building this?" The land is
 * public, so start there: a recorded deed names names. Then the question it
 * can't answer — who the Delaware buyer really is — opens onto a cluster of
 * shells whose shared agents and organizers are signals, not verdicts. A 2-up:
 * the deed, then the shell cluster, with the entity graph as the payoff.
 */
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import PathWayfinding from "../../components/PathWayfinding.astro";
import RecordTeardown from "../../components/RecordTeardown.astro";
import { DEED_TEARDOWN, SHELL_TEARDOWN } from "../../lib/teardowns";
import { chapterByStep, WALK_INDEX_HREF, walkHref } from "../../lib/walk";
import { withBase } from "../../lib/site";

const STEP = 1;
const prev = chapterByStep(STEP - 1);
const next = chapterByStep(STEP + 1);
---

<Base
  title="Who is actually building this? — Chapter 1"
  section="wiki"
  description="The land is public, so start there: a recorded deed names names. Then ask the question it can't answer — who the Delaware buyer really is."
>
  <div class="walk-chapter-page">
    <PathWayfinding step={STEP} />

    <div class="walk-chapter-eyebrow">Chapter {STEP} of 5 · the guided walk</div>
    <h1 class="walk-chapter-h1">Who is actually building this?</h1>

    <div class="walk-prose">
      <p>
        Start with the land, because the land is public. Every parcel that became
        the campus changed hands through a recorded deed — and recorded deeds name
        names. Read one, and then ask the question it can't answer: who is the
        buyer, really?
      </p>
    </div>

    <RecordTeardown record={DEED_TEARDOWN} layout="split" />

    <div class="td-beat">
      <div class="td-beat-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</div>
      <div class="td-beat-text">
        <b>and then —</b> the buyer is a Delaware shell, so the deed's “who” is
        really a question about a cluster of entities that share more than a state
        of formation.
      </div>
    </div>

    <RecordTeardown record={SHELL_TEARDOWN} layout="split" />

    <div class="walk-prose">
      <p>
        Hold the discipline here. Shared agents, shared organizers, a shared
        Wilmington mailbox — these are signals of coordination, the plumbing of
        common control. They are not, by themselves, proof of who owns or benefits.
        The record earns the word <em>signal</em>; it has not earned <em>verdict</em>.
        That distinction is the whole method — and it's why the buyer's name reads
        <code>[verified]</code> while the link between the shells reads
        <code>[inference]</code>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="callout walk-takeaway">
      <p class="callout-title">What you can read anywhere now</p>
      <p>
        A <strong>deed</strong> — grantor, grantee, parcels, and the consideration
        line, where a blank or nominal price is itself a finding. And a
        <strong>Secretary-of-State filing</strong> — the registered agent and
        organizer are how you link entities that share nothing else on their face.
        Overlaps are leads to verify, not conclusions to publish.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="walk-explore-h">Explore this in the library</h2>
    <div class="doors">
      <a class="door" href={withBase("/wiki/graph")}>
        <span class="door-label">The entity graph</span>
        <span class="door-blurb">The shells, their agents, and the overlaps — drawn so you can see them at once.</span>
      </a>
      <a class="door" href={withBase("/wiki/entities/")}>
        <span class="door-label">Entities</span>
        <span class="door-blurb">Bistrozzi, Tilted Gate, Magenta, and the people named on the filings.</span>
      </a>
      <a class="door" href={withBase("/site/records/")}>
        <span class="door-label">The deed records</span>
        <span class="door-blurb">The full conveyance chain — every parcel, grantor, and grantee.</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <nav class="walk-nav" aria-label="Chapter navigation">
      {
        prev?.live ? (
          <a class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-prev" href={walkHref(prev.slug)}>← {prev.step}. {prev.title}</a>
        ) : prev ? (
          <span class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-prev is-disabled" title="Drafting">← {prev.step}. {prev.title}</span>
        ) : (
          <a class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-prev" href={withBase("/start")}>← Start here</a>
        )
      }
      <a class="walk-nav-leave" href={WALK_INDEX_HREF}>All chapters</a>
      {
        next?.live ? (
          <a class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-next" href={walkHref(next.slug)}>{next.step}. {next.title} →</a>
        ) : next ? (
          <span class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-next is-disabled" title="Drafting">{next.step}. {next.title} →</span>
        ) : (
          <span></span>
        )
      }
    </nav>
  </div>
</Base>
